I have been to Starbucks in Iowa City before, the service is normally good due to the busy location on the college campus. I was greeted nicely and my order taken, this is where it went down hill, the young lady fixing the orders was not polite nor was she friendly. It took 12 minutes to get my French roast coffee and this is after I started timing the event , when it was put on the counter she was really having a bad day I said thank you and she gave me a glaring look. I went to the prepping station and there was no cream. I took the container to the counter and I was ignored several times I finally just left it on the counter and I had black coffee this Saturday. I will not use this Starbucks again I am on the campus almost every day as I work for the University. There are other places to purchase coffee and I think my money should be treated better than this. My not being a patron anymore will not change a thing for this location but how many patrons will you lose because of my visit? As I said before there are other places to purchase a cup of coffee.
